            </validTime>
          </tendency>
          <avActivityHighlights>The new snow and wind slabs represent the main danger. Above approximately 1800 m the wind slabs are larger. Wind slabs are to be evaluated with care and prudence.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In all aspects medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large slab avalanches are possible. In particular in the regions with a lot of snow the avalanches can penetrate even deep layers. As a consequence of solar radiation a very precarious avalanche situation will be encountered in some regions.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>A lot of snow has fallen over a wide area. In some places new snow and wind slabs are lying on a moist old snowpack. The high temperatures as the day progresses will give rise to rapid moistening of the snowpack on steep sunny slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
        </BulletinMeasurements>
